">Re: Quite possibly THE BEST Warrior items</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I agree with many of your points Kaoz, the difference between BP's isn't big enough to make one a clear choice over the other, it can definetly be argued both ways, as you did for warlords. However, let me throw in my viewpoint:<br>
<br>
Yes, Warlords has more ac. A pretty significant amount of it too. But it's not so much the hp to ac tradeoff that makes the Vind BP better, but the resists to ac tradeoff. You use BD jewelry as an example of items to raise resists. BD jewelry has sweet resists, yes, but NO ac. On a slot like earrings, for example, the tradeoff isn't so bad, I lose 2 ac and 35 hp for + resists to all. But let's look at say, the wrist slot. Using a BD wrist over Warlords, I'd lose 25 ac +stats for + resists to all. So yes, you gain 14 ac in non resist situtations, but lose 11 ac switching to resist gear for *ONE* slot.<br>
<br>
This part mainly applies to us in CQ, Kaoz, but I see in the upcoming months the North Wing in ToV and the Warders in ST as a focus of guild raids. All of which will require high resists. Stuff like the Dain, Vind, etc which we don't use resists on are already cake.<br>
<br>
Even if you don't use a BD wrist for resists and go with other items, in general using resist gear causes a significant loss of ac and hp to get to the 200 mark in resists (rune bone fork to idol, velium diamond rings to vel fire opal, etc). A Vind BP will greatly help in reducing ac and hp loss on raids, moreso than a Warlords BP in my opinion.<br>
<br>
As for stats, STR and DEX are very easy stats to get more of from other normal gear, with sham focus I'm at 254 already in DEX (thx epic) and at 245 in STR without relying on a Warlords BP. AGI is a bit harder to find, but it's effect on ac increase is small and shissar haste gives a good amount of AGI anyway.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think AoB is a crap effect and don't really take it into account anyway. But invigorate is really only good when soloing or during downtime on a raid, and I have a cobalt bp to provide my 100 hp heal.<br>
<br>
Zen, I can't find pics for gnome armor either, doesn't seem like Allak's site is updating the fashion table anymore. But here is what I have so far for warlords (gaunts, arms, legs). Pretty much guardian armor tinted blue/green. Myrmidion uses the other plate texture (same one as Beserkers), not sure if it's tinted though.<br>
<br>
