<br>
Your opinion can be applied to Yelinak's gauntlets, which would free up back/belt slots for things such as Dain belt or Cazic Cloak.<br>
<br>
But Dashel, if we'll be fighting a mob that requiers alot of resists, you will still be using a BD bracer <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and probably 2 of them. And a Tiara, and a Necklace. And whatever non-BD jewelry resist items there are. For some mobs you need skyhigh resists so AoE doesnt affect you as much. You'll be fighting in all your BD jewelry+Vind BP. I'll be fighting in all my BD jewelry+Warlords BP. You'll have 15 more resists probably. So yes, in those situations its more useful. But then again, we fight mobs that requiere specific resists like.. uh 20% of our raids. <br>
<br>
Although I agree, Vindicator's BP is very sweet, and there are 2 sides to which is better. I guess each for the situation. Doesn't mean I cant get a Vindicator's BP somewhere down the road. Hell, we're going to launch in a rocket to SoL soon, I'd better than that Fire resist up, never know with these gnome tinkered rockets <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Felwan, HP/AC/Resists should be basically your only concerns at high levels. I'm not going to say 'but its only 40hp!' because its as lame as saying 'but its only 4 to everything on the hiero' hehe. But again, you get a HP for AC tradeoff. And the AC trade seems to be greater to me. 14 raw AC become 22.4 AC on stats (using the rough formula of 1 ac x 1.6 = stat ac). And no matter how many HP you have, if your AC is low, all that HP not going to save you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . So its all matter of choice as you said. I preferred to go with Warlords, but maybe sometime down the road I might pickup Vindicator's BP too hehe.</font><P><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukaozator.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaozator</A> at: 5/7/01 3:47:54 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udashel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dashel</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>w4nn4b3!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>5/8/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>11:43:18 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quite possibly THE BEST Warrior items</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Aye, Kaoz, I'm not trying to slam your choice of warlords. It's a sweet BP and I'd love to have one. But unfortunetly there's only so much RPP we get and so many good items I'd like to have so I'll probably get Vind BP first and maybe a Warlords someday down the line. BD gear is nice, but I'd really like to get away from it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":